{
  "title": "Bitwise Logic",
  "guide": "### Truth Tables\nBit by bit operations.\n\n#### AND (&)\n1 only if **both** are 1.\n| A | B | Out |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| 1 | 0 | 0 |\n| 1 | 1 | **1** |\n\n#### OR (|)\n1 if **any** is 1.\n| A | B | Out |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| 1 | 0 | **1** |\n| 0 | 1 | **1** |\n\n#### XOR (^)\n1 if **different**.\n| A | B | Out |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| 0 | 0 | 0 |\n| 1 | 1 | 0 |\n| 1 | 0 | **1** |"
}
